<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee611858-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s940b"><num value="940b">§ 940b.</num><heading> Use of funds</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A borrower of an insured or guaranteed electric loan under this chapter may, without restriction or prior approval of the Secretary, invest its own funds or make loans or guarantees, not in excess of 15 percent of its total utility plant.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idee611859-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1936-05-20/ch432">May 20, 1936, ch. 432</ref>, title III, § 312, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/203/tI/s1402">Pub. L. 100–203, title I, § 1402</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1330-21">101 Stat. 1330–21</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/103/354/tII/s235/a/13">Pub. L. 103–354, title II, § 235(a)(13)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-13">Oct. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/3221">108 Stat. 3221</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
